    "They create two versions of MT-VAE.",
    "The first concatenates the motion features, whereas the second version sums them up.",
    "Motions are mainly gathered from 2D images and video sequences, but the extension to 3D pose descriptions is also possible.",
    "Another motion sequence generator is proposed by Petrovich et al. (2021), which, unlike previous methods, does not need initial poses to estimate diverse motions, Fig. 13.",
    "This is achieved by training an action-conditional generative model, with a transformer-based encoder-decoder network, hence the name: Action-conditioned Transformer VAE (ACTOR)."
